{
    "thought_on_cooking_style":"The cooking style in the provided recipes emphasizes simplicity and traditional techniques, focusing on the natural flavors of the ingredients. There's a clear preference for sauting, boiling, and baking, with attention to seasoning to enhance the taste. The recipes also show a tendency to use fresh herbs and a mix of textures, from creamy soups to crispy chicken skin. The style is homey and approachable, aiming to create comforting and satisfying meals.",
    "thought_on_recipe":"For the chicken pasta with peas recipe, I will follow the same principles of simplicity and flavor enhancement. The recipe will involve boiling pasta, sauting chicken, and incorporating peas for a fresh, green element. A light, creamy sauce will tie the dish together, seasoned with herbs and Parmesan cheese for depth. The steps will be clear and concise, allowing home cooks to easily follow and achieve a delicious result.",
    "recipe":
        {
            "title":"Creamy Chicken Pasta with Peas",
            "description":"This recipe brings together tender chicken, sweet peas, and pasta in a light creamy sauce, seasoned with Italian herbs and Parmesan cheese. It's a simple yet satisfying dish that's perfect for a weeknight dinner.",
            "list_of_steps": [
                {
                    "step": "Start by bringing a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add 12 ounces of your preferred pasta shape and cook according to the package instructions until al dente. Reserve 1 cup of pasta water before draining."
                },
                {
                    "step": "While the pasta cooks, cut 1 pound of boneless, skinless chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces. Season with salt, pepper, and a teaspoon of Italian seasoning."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the chicken pieces and saut until golden brown and cooked through, about 5-7 minutes. Remove the chicken from the skillet and set aside."
                },
                {
                    "step": "In the same skillet, add 1 cup of diced onions and saut until translucent. Add 2 cloves of minced garlic and cook for an additional minute until fragrant."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Stir in 1 cup of fresh or frozen peas and cook for 2-3 minutes until the peas are tender."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Reduce the heat to low and add 1/2 cup of heavy cream and 1/2 cup of grated Parmesan cheese to the skillet, stirring until the cheese is melted and the sauce is creamy."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Return the cooked chicken to the skillet and add the drained pasta. Toss everything together, adding a little reserved pasta water if needed to loosen the sauce."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Season the pasta with additional salt, pepper, and Italian seasoning to taste. Cook for another 2 minutes on low heat, allowing the flavors to meld."
                },
                {
                    "step": "Serve the creamy chicken pasta with peas hot, garnished with extra Parmesan cheese and a sprinkle of chopped parsley or basil for a fresh touch."
                }
            ]
        }
}
